summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 19,360, entitled: "An Ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of Orcas Street, in the City of Seattle, from the east line of Hillman City, Division No. 7, an Addition to the City of Seattle, to Lake Washington; and providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor; and providing that the payment for such improvement be made by special assessment upon property benefited, in the manner provided by law," approved on the 26th day of October, 1908.
